Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with analyzing internet activity records (IARs) of a mobile cellular network to understand network traffic patterns and optimize network resources. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the behavior of mobile users and how it can be identified using IAR data. This falls under the domain of social and information networks. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may also touch upon security concerns related to mobile traffic and how it can be partitioned to ensure secure communication. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a mobile traffic partitioning scheme which involves managing and optimizing network resources. This falls under the domain of systems and control. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper may also discuss the impact of mobile traffic on society and how it can be managed effectively.
